title.42: Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos Annual (1965) #7

description.0: The night of the Assassin! And, introducing the creature called- Baal!
description.1: At last! The Hulk finds Jarella, the girl from the emerald atom! But what's the difference, for tomorrow...the Sun dies!
description.3: The quest for the Well at the Edge of the World! The fury of Kartag the Keeper! And before your eyes...the fall of Asgard?
description.4: Torch and the Thing battle alongside the mysterious Black Panther- for a secret that may destroy the world! Plus a mystery super-villain!
description.7: The First Appearance of Werewolf By Night!  Jack Russell is heir to a strange lycanthropic curse…where upon he becomes the Werewolf by Night!
description.8: A spurned scientist devises a serum that gives him a monstrous appearance!
description.9: War - in the savage land at the bottom of the world! Ka-Zar and Zabu fight as never before! This one is action all the way, people!
description.16: The Black Widow is accused of murder...with Foggy Nelson for the prosecution! And if that isn't enough, here comes Mr. Hyde!
description.17: Androids replace our nation's leaders- for the deadliest purpose of all! The Hulk must right everyone else's wrongs. Plus, is this the end of the road for Doc Samson?
description.18: After nearly being defeated in his last battle with Mikas, the Gaurdsman rescues Tony Stark and takes him back to the Avengers Mansion. But when things look they're finally over, they're really just getting started.
description.20: The Thunder God battles to the death against the legendary Troll Legions- for the Well at World's End! And then...the return of Mangog!
description.21: Diablo vs. the Fantastic Four- in a battle that rocks the world! Plus, the Thing in solo action. Don't miss it!
description.22: Black Bolt - on the side of the murderous Magneto? It could happen - and all because of the Universe Machine!
description.23: Spider-Man and Ka-Zar must face the architect of Gwen's kidnapping: Kraven the Hunter!
description.24: It's the most cataclysmic climax of all when Cap and the Femme Force face off with HYDRA! But will they prevail over the forces of evil? Or will Steve Rogers lose the love of his life? Find out in this shocking issue!
description.29: Remember the Scorpion? Well, DD never met him, but he'll never forget him after this one!
description.30: The Leader makes a triumphant return with his wildest, most macabre scheme of all! And what can Greenskin do- especially with the world up in arms against him?
description.31: Worlds in agony! The climactic battle for the mystic Odin-Ring! And then...the wedding of Loki and Sif?!
description.32: Crystal's back...and Diablo's got her! The Human Torch lashes out to save his girlfriend- but will he succeed?
description.34: Man vs. Beast! Friends turned foes?! Ka-Zar and his companion, the last known Smilodon in existence, battle in a rage-fueled fight!
description.39: Spidey teams up with Ka-Zar and Zabu in the Savage Land!
description.40: Captain America and the Falcon split up! Introducing: the fantabulous Femme-Force! Plus, HYDRA, the most sinister of all insurrectionist organization are on the rise!
description.41: Witness the origin of the Defenders! But can the other heroes convince the Hulk to join the group?
description.48: Black Bolt and his Inhumans reunite just in time to face down the menace of Magneto!
description.51: Spidey had it bad dealing with his new transformation and fighting off Morbius at the same time, but the Lizard has shown up to make everything worse.
description.52: It can't be! It isn't possible! Not Him! Not the Red Skull!
description.53: Make way for the Black Widow! But, in the battle against the ominous Owl, whose side is she on? Plus, the secret of Mr. Kline revealed!
description.54: From a star beyond a star comes a power-mad Colossus! The Hulk must do battle as he never has before! But can even he hold out for long against...Godspawn?
description.55: The sinister plot to destroy Iron Man is revealed! Witness as a new Iron Man joins the fray! Don't miss the all-action issues when the Tony battles Mikas in their final showdown!
description.57: Enter- the Silver Surfer! Here begins the most mind-wrenching battle in the annals of timeless Asgard!
description.58: Impossible- but true! The new leader of the FF is...Doctor Doom? Plus, the sinister Stranger, and the end of the Over-Mind.
description.60: A scientist wants the strength of a gorilla…but at what cost?
description.62: It's Hulk's fight-to-the-finish with Dr. Doom! And this issue packs the wallop of a gamma-bomb blast! Will Latervia be spared once the dust settles?
description.63: Iron Man must put love on hold when Marianne becomes the new Demon-Queen! Will Tony Stark be able to save Marianne from herself? Or will the two end up killing each other in the end? Find out when Iron Man faces the Wail of the Demon-Queen!
description.65: The origin of the awesome Over-Mind! And Reed Richards turns against the FF!
description.70: An 8-limbed Spidey faces off against Morbius, the living vampire!
description.71: Captain America and the Falcon join forces with Nick Fury and Agent 13 in a final attempt to stop the Grey Gargoyle! Will their efforts prove to be successful? Or will the Grey Gargoyle destroy all they've sworn to protect?Don't miss this unbelievably ending!
description.76: He's back! The oh-so-ominous Owl, DD's most nefarious foe! And what he's got in store for Horn-Head is a force to be reckoned with!
description.77: This is it! Hulk finally meets Doctor Doom! But will these two titans clash in deadly battle...or team up to conquer mankind? Don't miss the shocking story arc, "Sanctuary"!
description.78: When two villains known as the Slasher and Demitrius target the Capital Building, Iron Man and his new love interest, Marianne Rodgers must team up to defeat them. Will they succeed? Or will they perish? Plus: Who is Mister Kiline?
description.80: Loki has the upper hand in a battle against his hated half-brother Thor! Loki's first order of business? Have Durok destroy the United Nations! His second? Make Sif his queen!
description.81: At last! This is your chance to learn more about the Over-Mind- one of the most exciting, dangerously different super-foes ever to menace the FF- and all of humanity.
description.84: Black Bolt vs. the Mighty Thor!
description.85: Peter creates a potion that will rid him of his powers. Upon drinking the potion, he finds that he's bitten off more than he can chew as he has grown four extra arms!
description.86: Elementary X is the most destructive substance known to man! Will Captain America be able to find and defeat the Grey Gargoyle before he gets to use it to destroy the world? Or will he lose his most trusted friends to the Gargoyle's stony grasp
description.89: The battle with the rampaging Man-Bull, plus a cataclysmic climax to end 'em all! Foggy Nelson is blackmailed by a sinister figure from his past!
description.90: Who would believe it? A fundraising party for the Hulk! Plus, the sensational return of the vengeful Valkyrie! And when these two meet it really packs a punch!
description.91: Iron Man puts his life on the line to save the U.N. when terrorist led by the White Dragon strike! Read and find out if Tony can stop this international threat in Night Walk!
description.93: Trickster Loki has seized the throne of Asgard! Durok the Destroyer comes to Earth!
description.94: The Thing lives! It's either prison or a life of crime for the FF! And then- meet the Overbrain! Guest-starring the Watcher.
description.95: Peter makes an honest attempt at getting a steady job. Meanwhile, Spider-Man appears on the Johnny Carson Show.
description.96: Cap and the Falcon find themselves going toe-to-toe with the Grey Gargoyle, a villain with the power to turn people into stone. Will Captain America and the Falcon be able to defeat this demon of the night?
description.99: Ka-Zar does not seem to have the same luck he had with Sun-God over Damon!

6.text: Namor's quest finally ends -- as he finds his long-lost father! But then, tragedy strikes -- not to mention the sensational Sting-Ray!

7.text: The first appearance, and origin!, of the Werewolf by Night! Jack Russell is heir to a strange lycanthropic curse...

9.text: War - in the savage land at the bottom of the world! Ka-Zar and Zabu fight as never before! This one is action all the way, people!

11.text: Maximus has taken over the city of the Inhumans! Where is Blackbolt when his people need him the most? Plus, The Avengers versus the Mandroids!
Maximus has taken over the city of the Inhumans! Where is Blackbolt when his people need him the most? Plus, The Avengers versus the Mandroids!

15.text: Namor and the Human Torch team up -- or do they? -- to face the vengeful Llyra and the man called Tiger Shark!

27.text: The Avengers have captured three Skrulls warriors! Though the Avengers have succeeded in turning the tables on the would-be alien conquerors, the heroes soon discover that The Vision has gone missing! Has he been captured?

The Avengers have captured three Skrulls warriors! Though the Avengers have succeeded in turning the tables on the would-be alien conquerors, the heroes soon discover that The Vision has gone missing! Has he been captured?

34.text: Man vs. Beast! Friends turned foes?! Ka-Zar and his companion, the last known Smilodon in existence, battle in a rage-fueled fight!

38.text: The President of the United States has issued an arrest warrant for Namor -- and the Feds don't care if he's brought in dead or alive!

44.text: A battle-damaged Vision arrives at Avengers Mansion and details the strange events that have befallen the team. Meanwhile, Captain Marvel and Carol Danvers are held prisoner by the Skrulls! Can Captain America, Thor, and Iron Man rescue them in time?

A battle-damaged Vision arrives at Avengers Mansion and details the strange events that have befallen the team. Meanwhile, Captain Marvel and Carol Danvers are held prisoner by the Skrulls! Can Captain America, Thor, and Iron Man rescue them in time?

47.text: "Mindquake!" Namor -- alone against Tuval, the Mind-Master! Plus, the startling re-appearance of two of Subby's most deadly foes!

50.text: Meet Johnny Wakely, the warrior Red Wolf, in his first ever appearance! And right off the bat, this hero of the American West faces personal tragedy!

67.text: This is it! Ka-Zar - Dr. Doom - plus a surprise all-new feature, just to kick things off!

69.text: "A House Called Death!" An entire city -- turned into monsters! Plus -- Namor takes on the Living Rock!

72.text: Anti-alien sentiment has spread across the nation! The Avengers must now answer to a governmental committee looking for an explanation as to the interactions between the Kree race and Earth's Mightiest.

Anti-alien sentiment has spread across the nation! The Avengers must now answer to a governmental committee looking for an explanation as to the interactions between the Kree race and Earth's Mightiest.

75.text: The start of a thunderous new epoch in the life of our avenging Atlantean! The quest for Namor's father -- plus the most startling villain of all!

87.text: Ronan The Accuser plans to de-evolve humanity into their ancestral simian form so that Earth may serve as a beachhead for the Kree-Skrull engagement. Can the Avengers stop Ronan and Sentry #459 without the help of the recently captured Mar-Vell?

Ronan The Accuser plans to de-evolve humanity into their ancestral simian form so that Earth may serve as a beachhead for the Kree-Skrull engagement. Can the Avengers stop Ronan and Sentry #459 without the help of the recently captured Mar-Vell?

98.text: Namor -- unwilling champion of a lost race, in a world where legend lives! The mind staggering mutant menace they call Turalla! All this -- and Spider-Man, too!

99.text: Ka-Zar does not seem to have the same luck he had with Sun-God over Damon!
